This paper deals with domain adaptation in the context of machine learning, specifically multi-class domain adaptation. The paper discusses the development of a new domain adaptation bound and algorithmic framework for multi-class UDA, which suggests adversarial learning objectives to align conditional feature distributions across domains. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
